\f0\fs24 \cf0 Project Outline (Detailed)\
\
This project is an educational, in-memory MiniSQL DBMS interpreter in Java.\
It parses a subset of SQL, builds AST nodes, and evaluates them against an in-process catalog.\
\
1. Purpose and Scope\
Primary purpose: implement a minimal DBMS pipeline end-to-end (lexing, parsing, semantic evaluation, and table operations).\
It is designed for learning/compiler-style architecture rather than production storage/query optimization.\
Evidence:\
CLI prompt and workflow in Main.java\
Grammar comments in GRAMMAR_PRODUCTIONS.java\
In-memory data structures in Catalog.java and Table.java\
2. High-Level Architecture\
LEXICAL/: tokenizer (Lexer) that emits Tokens from raw SQL input.\
SEMANTIC/PARSER/: recursive-descent parser (LL(1)-style) producing AST objects.\
SEMANTIC/AST_NODES/: statement and expression nodes with evaluate(...) logic.\
STRUCTURE/: runtime DB objects (Catalog, Table, Record, type wrappers).\
Converter/: conversion utility from AST schema nodes to runtime schema objects.\
BlueJ-centric project layout (package.bluej, .ctxt, many checked-in .class files).\
3. Runtime Flow (Request Lifecycle)\
Input is read from console in Main.java.\
Lexer scans text to tokens in Lexer.java.\
ParserContext manages current token and advancing in ParserContext.java.\
StatementListParser parses one or more statements ending with ; in StatementListParser.java.\
AST is evaluated (stmtlist.evaluate(db)), mutating/querying in-memory Catalog.\
4. Supported SQL Features\
CREATE TABLE table_name (col_name INT|STRING, ...)\
DROP TABLE table_name\
INSERT INTO table_name (value1, value2, ...)\
SELECT *|col1,col2 FROM table_name [WHERE col = literal [AND col = literal ...]]\
Keywords handled case-insensitively in lexer keyword map.\
WHERE supports only equality (=) and AND.\
Grammar is documented in GRAMMAR_PRODUCTIONS.java.\
5. Core Data Model\
Catalog stores tables in Map<String, Table> (uppercased keys) for case-insensitive lookup.\
Table stores:\
schema: List<Column>\
data: List<Record>\
Record stores HashMap<String, DBMSDataType> column-value pairs.\
Type system:\
interface DBMSDataType.java\
implementations MyInt.java, MyString.java\
6. AST and Evaluation Strategy\
Abstract base Statement.java with evaluate(Catalog).\
Concrete statements:\
CreateTableStatement.java\
InsertIntoStatement.java\
SelectStatement.java\
DropTableStatement.java\
Evaluation model is direct and imperative:\
no query planner\
no optimization layer\
direct traversal/filter/projection.\
7. Parser Design\
Recursive-descent parser split by nonterminal:\
statement parsers, condition parsers, literal/identifier parsers.\
ParserContext.expect(...) centralizes token expectation + error.\
Good separation between token stream handling and node creation.\
8. Coding Style and Engineering Patterns\
Strongly educational style:\
many explanatory comments\
clear one-class-per-concept decomposition\
explicit getters/setters everywhere\
Naming is mostly descriptive, but mixed conventions:\
table_name, column_type alongside camelCase\
package names uppercase (LEXICAL, SEMANTIC, STRUCTURE) which is unusual in Java style.\
Architecture is modular by concern, not layered with interfaces everywhere.\
Extensive BlueJ artifacts suggest classroom/project workflow.\
9. Error Handling\
Distinct exception classes:\
lexical: LexerException.java\
parse: ParseException.java\
runtime DB: DBMSException.java\
Main loop catches and prints user-facing errors.\
Type mismatch and schema mismatch checks are present in insert path.\
10. What Is Strong\
Clean educational decomposition of compiler pipeline.\
AST-driven execution is easy to extend.\
Type abstraction (DBMSDataType) is a good base for adding new types.\
SELECT flow has clear filtering + projection separation.\
11. Current Limitations / Gaps\
No persistence; everything is in memory and lost on exit.\
No UPDATE/DELETE/ALTER/JOIN/OR/comparison operators beyond =.\
No indexes or performance optimizations.\
No formal test suite framework (only simple lexer test main).\
Repo contains compiled artifacts (.class) and IDE metadata.\
I observed a runtime stdin issue in this execution environment when trying non-interactive piping, so CLI robustness around EOF may need hardening in Main.java.\
12. Project Composition Snapshot\
Java source files: 59\
Checked-in .class files: 66\
BlueJ .ctxt files: 57\
UML assets present in /Users/megha_shah/Documents/Ren_Proj/DBMS/UML Images\
13. Architecture Summary in One Line\
Interpreter architecture: SQL text -> Lexer -> Recursive-descent Parser -> AST -> Evaluate on in-memory Catalog/Table/Record model. \
